RIYADH: Saudi Arabia’s Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman on Friday held a phone call with French President Emmanuel Macron to discuss the repercussions of the Russia-Ukraine war. Also during the call,  the crown prince expressed his congratulations to Macron on his re-election, Saudi Press Agency reported. They reviewed Saudi-French relations, emphasized the strategic partnership between the two countries, and discussed the latest regional and international developments, and the efforts made in their regard to achieve security and stability. Prince Mohammed also discussed with Macron way to calm the tension in Ukraine, the Elysee palace said.